A former minister of Aviation, Femi Fani-Kayode, has upbraided those peddling the death rumour of chief of staff to the president, Abba Kyari, saying they are “vicious and heartless”. There had been a rumour mostly on social media that the president’s henchman who tested positive for the disease last week had died from COVID-19 complications. In a tweet on Thursday, Fani-Kayode described those wishing Kyari dead because they disagree with him as vicious. The former minister said however that he remains opposed to the administration of President Muhammadu Buhari. “It is not true that Abba Kyari, the Chief of Staff to @MBuhari, is dead. Those that are behind that rumour are vicious and heartless. I remain opposed to the @MBuhari admin. But to wish or proclaim someone dead simply because you disagree with him politically is unacceptable,” he tweeted. Meanwhile, a Non-Governmental Organization known as One Destiny Organization (ODO) has outlined prayer sessions and programmes to seek God’s intervention in containing the ravaging COVID-19 pandemic in Nigeria and beyond. The executive director of One Destiny Organization, Ohiri O. Lewis, who disclosed this to newsmen in Owerri after inspecting the brand new Isolation Center with world class medical equipment being constructed by the Lagos State Government at Onikan Stadium, Lagos, said they are using Alhaji Abba Kyari, the Chief of Staff to President Muhammadu Buhari, who recently tested positive to the virus but now recovering quickly as a ‘point of contact’ to reach and pray for the recovery of other infected persons in Nigeria and globally. “We in One Destiny Organization have resolved to enter into prayer sessions and spiritual programs to ultimately seek the face of God and His spiritual intervention while our nation under President Mohammadu Buhari and health professionals work assiduously to contain this dreaded virus.”